House Bill 888
By: Representative Carpenter of the 4th
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Title 20 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to education, so as to
2 provide for in-state tuition for postsecondary education for certain noncitizen students; to
3 provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
5 SECTION 1.
6 Title 20 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to education, is amended in
7 Code Section 20-3-66, relating to determination of in-state resident status of students in the
8 University System of Georgia for tuition or fees, by revising subsection (e) as follows:
9 "(e)(1) Noncitizen students shall not be classified as in-state for tuition purposes unless
10 the student is legally in this state and there is evidence to warrant consideration of in-state
11 classification as determined by the board of regents.:
12 (A) Obtained a high school diploma or state approved high school equivalency (HSE)
13 diploma in this state;
14 (B) Is legally authorized to work in this state;
