15 (C) Has independently established and maintained domicile in this state since
16 January 1, 2020, or is the dependent child of a parent who has established and
17 maintained domicile in this state since January 1, 2020;
18 (D) Has not been convicted of a felony or a high and aggravated misdemeanor; and
19 (E) Is enrolled in or applying for admission to an institution of the University System
20 of Georgia which, for the two most recent academic years, admitted all academically
21 qualified applicants.
22 (2) Lawful permanent residents, refugees, asylees, or other eligible noncitizens as
23 defined by federal Title IV regulations may be extended the same consideration as
24 citizens of the United States in determining whether they qualify for in-state
25 classification.
26 (3) International students who reside in the United States under nonimmigrant status
27 conditioned at least in part upon intent not to abandon a foreign domicile shall not be
28 eligible for in-state classification."
29 SECTION 2.
30 Said title is further amended in Code Section 20-4-21, relating to tuition fees in the Technical
31 College System of Georgia, by adding a new subsection to read as follows:
32 "(e) Notwithstanding any other law to the contrary, the State Board of the Technical
33 College System of Georgia shall classify a noncitizen student as in-state for tuition
34 purposes if the student:
35 (1) Obtained a high school diploma or state approved high school equivalency (HSE)
36 diploma in this state;
37 (2) Is legally authorized to work in this state;
38 (3) Has independently established and maintained domicile in this state since January 1,
39 2020, or is the dependent child of a parent who has established and maintained domicile
40 in this state since January 1, 2020;
